# Slashing — Formal Verification
#
# Establishes observational bisimilarity at the process level between
# the Rust slashing logic in this repository and the Scala original,
# with explicit, proven bug-fix deltas where the Scala source is faulty.
#
# Source: f1r3node-rust/casper/src/rust/{equivocation_detector,validate,
#         multi_parent_casper_impl,blocks/proposer/block_creator,
#         util/rholang/costacc/slash_deploy}.rs
# Companion docs:
#   docs/theory/slashing/slashing-specification.md  (normative spec)
#   docs/theory/slashing/slashing-verification.md   (proofs in math + Rocq pointers)
#
# 21 modules. Zero `Admitted`. Four classical lemmas cited inline:
#   (a) Sangiorgi's bisimulation up-to expansion
#       [San98] DOI 10.1017/S0960129598002527
#   (b) Newman's lemma (confluence + termination ⇒ Church-Rosser)
#   (c) König's lemma (finitely-branching infinite tree has infinite branch)
#   (d) f < n/3 BFT bound
#       [LSP82] DOI 10.1145/357172.357176
#
# Module dependency graph (→ = "depends on"):
#
#   Validator              (standalone)
#   Block                  → Validator
#   InvalidBlock           → Block
#   EquivocationRecord     → Validator, Block
#   DAGState               → Block, EquivocationRecord
#   EquivocationDetector   → DAGState, InvalidBlock
#   PoSContract            → Validator
#   SlashDeploy            → Block, PoSContract, InvalidBlock
#   BlockCreator           → DAGState, SlashDeploy, EquivocationRecord
#   ForkChoice             → DAGState, PoSContract
#   TwoLevelSlashing       → EquivocationDetector, SlashDeploy, ForkChoice
#   BugFixIgnorable        → EquivocationDetector, EquivocationRecord
#   BugFixAtomicTracker    → EquivocationRecord, DAGState
#   BugFixDispatcher       → InvalidBlock, EquivocationDetector, SlashDeploy
#   BugFixTransferFailure  → PoSContract, SlashDeploy
#   BugFixStakeZero        → EquivocationDetector, PoSContract
#   BugFixSelfRegression   → DAGState, Block
#   BugFixSeqNumDensity    → EquivocationDetector, Block
#   BugFixUnbondedProposer → BlockCreator, PoSContract
#   Bisimulation           → all of the above (the headline relation)
#   MainTheorem            → Bisimulation, all BugFix*
#
# The development assumes the on-chain Rholang `slash` contract at
# `casper/src/main/resources/PoS.rhox:432-495` as a shared implementation
# between Scala and Rust — the contract is loaded into the Rust interpreter
# unmodified. Bug fix #4 (PoS.rhox:469 transfer-failure FIXME) therefore
# applies to both sides equally.
#
# Bisimilarity is defined modulo:
#   - α-equivalence on Rholang names
#   - iteration order on BTreeSet (Rust) vs Set (Scala) — value-level only,
#     not byte-level on-disk

